{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17600053","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17600053"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:00:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:00:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15603"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15603","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15603"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0.1,0.48,0.43]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8294"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66630"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8294","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8294"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15603"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52083"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7005"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8218"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20021"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20023"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22236"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66630","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66630"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman presents for evaluation of thyroid enlargement noted by her general practitioner.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following findings is most suggestive of thyroid malignancy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Diffuse thyroid enlargement","Tender thyroid gland","Mobile nodule on examination","Firm focal mass","Hot nodule on nuclear scan"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhen evaluating thyroid nodules, certain characteristics increase suspicion for malignancy. A \u003Cstrong\u003Efirm focal mass\u003C/strong\u003E is concerning as it suggests invasion or fibrosis associated with cancer. In contrast, \u003Cstrong\u003Ediffuse thyroid enlargement\u003C/strong\u003E is more typical of benign conditions like goitre or thyroiditis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Etender thyroid gland\u003C/strong\u003E typically suggests inflammation rather than cancer, as seen in subacute thyroiditis. \u003Cstrong\u003EHot nodules\u003C/strong\u003E on nuclear scanning represent areas of autonomous function and are usually benign adenomas. A \u003Cstrong\u003Emobile nodule\u003C/strong\u003E that moves with swallowing is typically benign, while malignant nodules often become fixed to surrounding structures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A firm, focal thyroid mass is more concerning for malignancy than diffuse enlargement or tender/painful swelling.","Hot nodules on thyroid scans are typically benign and represent autonomous functioning tissue."],"references":["Shah JP. Thyroid carcinoma: epidemiology, histology, and diagnosis. Clin Adv Hematol Oncol. 2015 Apr;13(4 Suppl 4):3-6. PMID: 26430868; PMCID: PMC5526593","Kitahara CM, Schneider AB. Epidemiology of Thyroid Cancer. Cancer Epidemiol Biomarkers Prev. 2022 Jul 1;31(7):1284-1297. doi: 10.1158/1055-9965.EPI-21-1440. PMID: 35775227; PMCID: PMC9473679","Boucai L, Zafereo M, Cabanillas ME. Thyroid Cancer: A Review. JAMA. 2024 Feb 6;331(5):425-435. doi: 10.1001/jama.2023.26348. PMID: 38319329","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell